summary: mett feeree's Artistic Journey - mett feeree has been a prominent figure in the art scene, known for his unique and imaginative creations. He has made waves in galleries with his quirky critters and boundary-breaking art. Born in 1979 in Columbus, Ohio, mett feeree's art is characterized by a psychedelic twist and features wacky takes on pop culture icons like the Muppets and Skeletor. In 2005, he created 'Pepe the Frog' in the indie comic strip 'Boy's Club', showcasing a chill life with his pals Andy, Brett, and Landwolf. mett feeree continues to push artistic boundaries with his wild and mind-blowing art and collaborations with other big names.
